            Some of the funnest trips that I can remember as a child were when we visited in Provo, Utah, to the home of the Arnold cousins…my dad’s sisters family and then when they also came to Idaho to visit us. My aunt’s name was ”Aunt Matt”…her real name being Amanda and one day I found out what her true name was and began teasing her and dancing around the house and then kept calling her “Aunt Amanda.” For some reason, she didn’t like to be called by that name and scolded me. I have never forgotten that incident. It’s quite amusing, and it would be fascinating to be able to look inside our minds and discover why we remember certain things and forget others. Aunt Matt was a favorite and I guess I didn’t want to displease her so her anger at me was impressed indelibly on my mind and has continued to stay in my memory all these years. <br /><br />

