                    We always had a theme for our reunions, and everyone in the family participated. We had committees. Everyone was part of a committee, preparing meals and preparing games to play. The food was a big deal. We always tried to have special food that everyone would enjoy. We often had the food catered, but mostly family wanted to work together, to be together, and to have fun together. Our family has always had those blessings of enjoying being together and looking forward to reunion time. We had about half a dozen reunions here in this home. <br /><br />

                    I think reunions are a very special part of family relationships. They bring families together; for those who’ve lived far away and been separated for a number of years, when they come to a reunion—I don't know how to describe it. It's such a warm, special time to be together with those that you love and be part of a very special family. We have always enjoyed having the reunions.<br /><br />

