            Many enjoyable hours during my childhood (mid-young teen years) were spent in my room reading. I loved to read and can remember at times my mother would have to come to my room and take my book so I would come to the table to eat! Most of my books were from the Idaho Falls Public Library and my memory holds many feelings of enjoyable hours reading books. <br /><br />

            I didn’t own many books of my own but had good friends willing to share. I was especially fond of the “Nancy Drew” mystery series and longed to have the new one when it came out and then the next one and the next. I was always trying to find someone who had the book so I could persuade them to lend it to me. I remember one day gaining enough courage to ask a friend of mine for several of them as she was from a “rich” family and dream of all dreams she had the whole series on her bookshelves. Her house was a very big house or so it seemed to me then, and I went bravely over. She was sick in bed; her mother led me up the stairs and there the “princess” lay in her bed sick. I stumbled over the words, “Can I borrow some of your Nancy Drew books…?” And she lent them to me. (I have driven by that house since becoming an adult and that house isn’t so big after all!)

